Description: Fragment of sub-round handle at neck join to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-brown; dull white slip.
Curator's comments: Name Menogenes. Ink mark '7', underscored; pencil mark '7'. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0386.41.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1176)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
